He visto que la varios de moders no saben como tomar sus capturas al momento de presentar sus mods, por ello he hecho este mapa(en realidad modificado)

Detalles:

1. El mapa es una adaptación y modificación de otro mapa con el mismo propósito, este mapa provenia del Workshop del videojuego "Codename Cure", el mapa original tenía el nombre de "cbe_cubecase"

2. Este mapa posee 3 salas, 1 central, para los spawns, y 2 para la demostración, uno de ellos posee 
un entorno oscuro con una luz vertical en el centro, la otra posee un entorno rodeado de skybox por si se desea algo más elegante(?), todas las salas poseen una zona de compra.

Ok, this is a new type of map, a new game play, and one I hope to make preety popular. It's called Deer Hunt. The point of the game is for the deer (Terrorists) to kill the hunter (counter-terrorist) and make it over to his side before the round starts over to steal some weapons for an advantage for the next round. It might sound crazy, but give it a try. There is an invisible wall keeping the deer and the hunter from shooting at eachother when they spawn - to open this wall, press one of the buttons, they are preety easy to see as they stand out. I have ideas on a fort one, where deer start outside the fort and the hunter is inside, and the deer must get in the fort and steal the weapons. 

Have fun and leave feedback.

Oh and one more thing, could I somehow get my own category is I keep making these kinds of maps? Such as Fight Yard and Prepared Assault maps did?

//==================================\\
|| DB_DODGEBALL README
\\==================================//

Dodgeball Arena
-- Author: free(ghost)
-- Date: 03/17/09
-- Version: 1.0 Beta

I noticed a growing population in the dodgeball area of Counter-Strike,
and I had a request to make a professional league arena. So I did and I
figured I could upload it here for anyone who wishes to play some dodgeball
in an indoor-style arena.

Map layout is roughly based off of a basketball court / dodgeball court.

NOTE: This is meant for LEAGUE use... some people may use the stands as a way
to avoid grenades. Since this is beta, I figured I'd let you decide if I should
keep them or not.

Thanks, and enjoy!
-free
